WEBVTT

00:00.016 --> 00:01.375
Who's up for Chinese checkers?

00:01.438 --> 00:03.164
Oh, half the marbles are missing.

00:03.219 --> 00:05.171
Everyone, spread out
and find a suitable replacement

00:05.226 --> 00:06.434
for the red and white ones.

00:06.481 --> 00:08.265
And a suitable replacement
for a pet in this house.

00:08.314 --> 00:11.377
Something snobby and purebred,
with lots of health issues

00:11.417 --> 00:13.541
so it dies before I get bored with it.

00:16.239 --> 00:18.112
You hurt his feelings!

00:18.180 --> 00:19.580
Don't you have a heart?

00:19.682 --> 00:22.449
He does, and it's just covered
under layers of snark.

00:23.486 --> 00:25.753
Taylor, it's game night.
Do you want to join us?

00:25.821 --> 00:27.521
Don't be ridiculous.

00:27.590 --> 00:29.390
I'm going downtown with my friends.

00:29.458 --> 00:31.992
Have fun with your little games.

00:33.129 --> 00:35.529
I do not like what our nice,
fun-loving Taylor has become

00:35.598 --> 00:37.598
since she started hanging out
with these popular girls.

00:37.700 --> 00:39.400
This is the way she walks around school

00:39.502 --> 00:40.934
with her stuck-up friends...

00:42.638 --> 00:44.672
- Excellent pantomime work.
- Mm-hmm.

00:48.944 --> 00:50.044
Spencer!

00:50.146 --> 00:51.812
I've got big news!

00:51.914 --> 00:53.947
Wait for it.

00:54.050 --> 00:55.415
Wait for it.

00:55.461 --> 00:57.169
Ta-da!

00:57.238 --> 00:59.672
Please tell me this has
nothing to do with Viagra.

00:59.741 --> 01:04.275
No, my house-arrest ankle
bracelet isn't beeping anymore.

01:04.345 --> 01:06.012
That's because I don't have one.

01:06.080 --> 01:07.380
I'm a free man!

01:07.448 --> 01:08.814
Congratulations!

01:08.883 --> 01:10.316
Tomorrow we golf. You got clubs?

01:10.385 --> 01:11.584
No.

01:11.653 --> 01:13.519
I'm buying you clubs.
Can I buy him clubs?

01:13.588 --> 01:15.321
- Um...
- I'm buying you clubs!

01:15.390 --> 01:18.124
You know, you got a good kid here.

01:18.192 --> 01:20.059
A true friend, which is hard to find.

01:20.209 --> 01:21.942
Because when you're rich,

01:22.044 --> 01:24.411
people are always trying
to get close to you.

01:24.480 --> 01:27.181
Biggie called it...
mo money, mo problems.

01:27.249 --> 01:28.549
Oliver, be ready.

01:28.617 --> 01:31.085
I got us a tee time...
9:00 a.m., Longshore.

01:31.153 --> 01:33.053
- You got golf shoes?
- No.

01:33.122 --> 01:34.421
I'm buying you golf shoes.

01:34.490 --> 01:35.923
I'm buying him golf shoes!

01:36.058 --> 01:37.558
Ha-ha!

01:37.626 --> 01:39.560
You hear what he said?

01:39.628 --> 01:41.161
I'm a good kid.

01:41.230 --> 01:43.530
Yeah, I'm not buyin' it.

