16:31.537 --> 16:33.370
- Mm-hmm.
- He does, doesn't he?

16:34.407 --> 16:36.507
Okay, we've been here long enough.

16:36.609 --> 16:39.009
Just say goodbye and we can
get on with our lives.

16:39.111 --> 16:41.712
Come on.

16:42.882 --> 16:45.783
Hans Gruber,
I'm gonna miss you, big guy.

16:45.885 --> 16:48.185
♪ Me and you, and you and me ♪

16:48.254 --> 16:51.722
♪ No matter how they toss
the dice, it had to be ♪

16:51.791 --> 16:53.824
Yep. That was our jam.

16:54.994 --> 16:56.660
Bye, Hans.

16:56.729 --> 16:59.296
I know we didn't start out
the best of friends,

16:59.365 --> 17:00.764
but you grew on me.

17:00.866 --> 17:03.133
The night I ate
all those Girl Scout Cookies,

17:03.202 --> 17:05.970
I looked over and saw you
chewing on a used coffee filter.

17:06.038 --> 17:08.973
I feel like you did it to make
me feel better about myself.

17:09.040 --> 17:11.909
And it worked, so thank you.

17:16.915 --> 17:18.482
Goodbye, Hans Gruber.

17:18.550 --> 17:20.117
At least you can make friends here

17:20.219 --> 17:21.551
without your parents butting in

17:21.621 --> 17:23.252
and deciding who's best for you.

17:27.859 --> 17:30.094
So this is it.
When Daddy brought you home,

17:30.129 --> 17:32.529
you got a second chance at life,
and I got a chance

17:32.598 --> 17:35.111
to know what real
friendship is all about.

17:36.252 --> 17:38.902
I'm gonna miss your
snorts and your nose kisses.

17:38.938 --> 17:42.072
I'm gonna miss playing fetch
with Daddy's hairbrush.

17:42.141 --> 17:44.141
- What did she just say?
- Shh.

17:44.210 --> 17:46.243
Be a good pig.

17:46.312 --> 17:48.879
And I'll be back to visit
before you know it.

17:55.721 --> 17:58.355
You did good, baby.

